<TEXT>
johnny isakson is attacking georgias old boy 
network in a bid to become the states first republican governor 
since reconstruction but he faces an uphill fight against lt gov 
zell miller 
isakson the state house minority leader has accused miller and 
others of squandering tax dollars to build individual offices for 
state legislators while leaving some schoolchildren to attend class 
in trailers 
miller and his democratic gubernatorial campaign branded 
isaksons ad an exercise in rank hypocrisy isakson has two 
state offices and even voted for the budget that financed the 
legislative office construction millers statement said 
miller has been lieutenant governor for 16 years but isakson 
isnt a newcomer to state government either the prosperous atlanta 
real estate executive has been a state legislator since 1976 
miller is a former marine rifle range instructor who talks tough 
on drugs while promising a sales tax exemption for food 
isakson has a reputation as a solid nononsense legislator and 
his contacts in the business community are counted as a plus 
but isakson must overcome the momentum miller built during his 
drive for the democratic nomination and state voters preference 
for democrats in top state offices 
without question its still zells to lose said atlanta 
pollster claibourne darden 
isaksons media consultant robert goodman disagrees saying 
the democrat is vulnerable 
miller has been running as a media candidate trying to pose as 
the champion of change said goodman but zell miller is part 
of the old boy network as you will see as the campaign evolves 
miller has political ties to highway builders and other 
interests and until this year used a lakeside lot leased from a 
utility 
miller outnumbers isakson 21 in staff and money political 
consultant james carville heads the democrats campaign stressing 
opposition research 
it is hard for somebody to hit you when you have your fist in 
their face carville has been quoted as saying 
president bush plans to host a 1500percouple fundraiser for 
isakson who had raised 2 million through july compared with 44 
million for miller 
miller swept away five democratic primary challengers 
including atlantas former mayor andrew young by promising to 
legalize state lotteries 
miller said his campaign emerged from the primary in good shape 
and is as strong as garlic in a milkshake 
isakson had little trouble dispatching three rivals to win the 
gop nomination then took a back seat while miller and young fought 
a runoff battle 
miller usually has allowed his aides to answer isakson and has 
been adept at focusing attention on his favorite issues especially 
his proposal for a state lottery 
when the candidates appeared together at a forum before 
educators miller stole the headlines by proposing that parents be 
allowed to choose which public schools their children should 
attend 
state spending is a key issue for isakson who for years as 
house republican leader criticized georgias spending process as 
lacking discipline and priorities often the dissent fell on deaf 
ears because the republican minority had little legislative impact 
on state government and because of isaksons penchant of attacking 
with a barrage of statistics 
this year democrats have served the issue to him on a platter 
just a year after passing the biggest tax increase in state history 
a onecent sales tax increase to finance prisons schools and 
health needs the state must cut spending by 332 million because 
of an economic slowdown 
isakson still employs some of his old techniques of responding 
to the issue with detail recently releasing a 13page budget 
policy statement but he also has gotten media savvy in the age of 
the 30second sound bite 
its up to johnny to use the old george patton technique 
attack attack attack said darden if johnny doesnt hes 
gone he has to attack and show zell is not the one to vote for 
and by default johnny is 
