<TEXT>
five years and 15 million ago the federal 
government issued its only official earthquake prediction the 
central california town of parkfield would be severely shaken by 
1993 
recent rumblings suggest the forecast soon may come true 
they definitely elevate my belief that the earthquake is 
likely to happen in the next few months said evelyn roeloffs 
scientist in charge of the us geological surveys parkfield 
earthquake prediction experiment 
after a threeyear lull seismic activity increased during the 
summer and particularly this month near tiny parkfield the town is 
halfway between los angeles and san francisco in grassy oakdotted 
ranchland of the cholame valley which straddles the mighty san 
andreas fault 
it was in the valley that actor james dean died in a 1955 car 
crash 
moderate to strong quakes measuring 55 to 63 on the richter 
scale have ruptured a 20milelong section of the fault near 
parkfield roughly every 22 years since 1857 the most recent was in 
1966 the quakes caused little damage in the valley where about 
200 people now live 
the temblors regularity prompted a 1985 geological survey 
prediction that another magnitude6 quake was 95 percent likely 
during a 10year period centered around january 1988 which meant 
by no later than january 1993 
the parkfield prediction is the only one ever issued by the 
federal government and ndorsed by california and federal 
scientific panels 
the geological survey has spent 15 million installing scores of 
seismometers and other sensors and instruments near parkfield 
making it the most heavily instrumented piece of fault in the 
world survey spokeswoman pat jorgenson said 
researchers hope the sensors will help them recognize changes in 
the earth in the months days hours and minutes before the 
predicted magnitude6 jolt allowing them to issue a shortterm 
public warning 
im not hoping to rain death and destruction on parkfield but 
im hoping we can have the event we set up all this instrumentation 
to catch roeloffs said by phone from menlo park 
the predicted quake is not expected to cause significant damage 
said richard andrews chief deputy director of californias office 
of emergency services 
he said it could shake things off shelves and damage chimneys in 
parkfield and surrounding towns such as paso robles avenal 
coalinga and atascadero 
the streams of scientists visiting parkfield spurred rancher 
jack varians family to open the towns only cafe and start 
building a fourroom motel 
a sign outside the restaurant says parkfield cafe parkfield 
calif earthquake capital of the world be here when it happens 
varians 27yearold son john is excited about the impending 
quake but i just want it to wait until march until the motels 
open 
ill be darned if im going to hope for an earthquake said 
parkfield school teacher duane hamann who works parttime making 
measurements for scientists things are going to fly all over the 
place 
to help people protect themselves the geological survey and 
state officials established a warning system in which alerts are 
triggered by various combinations of small quakes and other signs 
the highest alert known as levela will spur officials to 
issue a public warning that the predicted quake is at least 37 
percent likely within three days 
since 1986 there have been no levela or b alerts 22 levelc 
alerts and 53 leveld alerts roeloffs said 
the latest levelc alert a warning that the quake is between 3 
and 11 percent likely within three days was issued sept 9 
roeloffs said the alert was triggered by a magnitude33 quake 
north of parkfield on sept 9 and an unusual rise in well water 
levels 
another 33 quake rattled the area sept 10 the small quakes 
were followed by numerous aftershocks and by magnitude22 quakes 
sept 14 and 15 
there also was a steady increase in magnitude3 quakes all 
summer farther northwest of parkfield a pattern roeloffs called 
similar to the seismicity in the six months before the 1966 
earthquake 
geological survey scientists have said there is a 2 percent to 
10 percent chance the parkfield quake could grow into or trigger a 
major magnitude7 jolt 
if that happened parkfield and surrounding towns might 
experience considerable damage especially to unreinforced brick 
buildings according state officials slight damage might occur as 
far away as san luis obispo hollister bakersfield and fresno 
in 1857 a moderate parkfield quake was followed within hours by 
an earthquake exceeding magnitude 8 that ruptured a 200mile 
stretch of the san andreas from south of parkfield to the los 
angeles area recent studies however show that is extremely 
unlikely to happen after the next parkfield quake 
other studies raise doubts about the parkfield prediction 
previous parkfield quakes around magnitude6 happened in 1857 
1881 1901 1922 but then the pattern was broken with one in 1934 
10 years early however the next magnitude6 quake waited until 
1966 seeming to restore the original pattern 
geological survey geophysicist jim savage argues that 
uncertainty created by the timing of the 1934 quake means the 
likelihood the parkfield quake will happen by 1993 is only 60 
percent 
</TEXT>
