losses seem to have leveled out at the 
nations privately run savings institutions but analysts say the 
spread of weak real estate markets could produce another slide 
the 2437 sampls outside government control lost 196 million in 
the apriljune period the office of thrift supervision said 
monday 
that was a modest improvement over the 219 million loss in the 
first three months of the year it also was a dramatic gain over 
the 720 million loss in the last three months of 1989 but a 
substantial deterioration from the 308 million profit earned by 
the same institutions a year earlier 
its very difficult to predict that the trend of reduced 
losses in the industry will continue or that the industry as a 
whole will become profitable this year thrift office director 
timothy ryan said 
he noted a real disparity in thrift performance 
geographically thrifts in the pacific northwest and in the upper 
midwest continue to be profitable largely because these areas have 
so far escaped the real estate downturn experienced in the 
southwest and more recently the northeast 
