us officials hope an international food 
relief effort can get under way in angola within the next 30 to 60 
days to prevent widespread starvation 
the crisis is upon us and we must act now said andrew 
natsios head of the us office of foreign disaster assistance 
angolan officials have committed themselves to a un plan that 
would permit emergency food deliveries from third countries 
the leftist government had been worried that the united states 
might use food deliveries to send weapons to the anticommunist 
unita rebels 
natsios was snubbed by angolan officials two weeks ago during a 
visit to luanda the capital they had a change of heart last week 
and agreed in a communique to allow the prompt and efficient 
delivery of food supplies to tens of thousands of angolans who 
face starvation because of drought 
