<TEXT>
british journalist harold king who covered the 
battle of stalingrad and forged close ties with french leader 
charles de gaulle has died he was 91 
the reuters news agencys paris bureau which king headed from 
1944 to 1967 said he died monday at a clinic at nogentsurmarne 
near paris 
he died of heart failure following surgery for a bladderrelated 
ailment the british agency said 
harold was larger than life commanding attention and respect 
among journalists in political circles and among the best 
restaurants in europe reuters managing director glen renfrew 
commented in london 
king was born harold koenig in berlin in 1898 the family moved 
to london and his father a german psychiatrist changed the family 
name to king when world war i broke out in 1914 
king began his literary career in 1919 as secretary to writer 
jerome k jerome author of three men in a boat 
but he quickly shifted to journalism and moved to paris in 1931 
where he became correspondent for the wall street journal and the 
financial times 
king fled paris for london in 1940 as hitlers armies stormed 
across france he then began his long career with reuters covering 
gen de gaulles exiled french forces 
reuters later sent king to the soviet union where he wrote on 
the red army victory at stalingrad and covered stalins breakup of 
the communist international in 1943 
king accompanied the free french landings in southern france in 
1944 
he cultivated his contacts with de gaulle during the generals 
postwar withdrawal from political life france recalled him as 
president in 1958 during the height of the algerian war 
the two men enjoyed close relations and king became one of de 
gaulles favorite media contacts 
after king stepped down as head of the paris bureau the agency 
named him honorary assistant director for life he later worked as 
a correspondent for the toronto telegram 
france named king a commander of the legion of honor one of the 
countrys highest honors in 1971 
king had been in failing health for about a decade his recent 
surgery followed a broken hip suffered in a fall a few weeks ago 
his wife the romanian dancer irene codreanu died in 1985 the 
couple had no children funeral arrangements were not immediately 
announced 
</TEXT>
