<TEXT>
editors note this is one of a series of stories on the german 
countdown to unity on oct 3 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
prime minister lothar de maiziere said today 
that east germans fear for their futures in a united germany and 
that social guarantees are needed to ease the move to a new 
society 
in a wideranging conversation with the associated press board 
of directors de maiziere also said the lingering specter of the 
former secret police is one of the most difficult legacies we 
have from the communist past 
east germanys first freely chosen leader in an address and 
during a questionandanswer session outlined his hopes for his 16 
million people as they move closer to german unification on oct 3 
he said east germans had the misfortune of living for four 
decades under a government in which their futures were decided by 
the communist hierarchy 
a tremendous obstacle will be teaching them to take control of 
their destinies to live successful lives in the competitive 
freemarket society epitomized by west germany he said 
the future in the past meant the future prescribed by the 
politburo he said now the people see their future is not a 
prescribed time but a free time this is something people did not 
learn and they are afraid of that 
he said the future government of a united germany must have a 
strong social consciousness to help east germans make the 
transition 
he also said the files on 6 million people compiled by the 
notorious secret police known as the stasi and the tens of 
thousands of people who worked for them are among the most 
difficult problems confronting the new society 
he said german law enforcment officials should have access to 
those files to punish people who committed crimes for the stasi 
and to rehabilitate people whose lives were ruined by the dreaded 
security apparatus 
but there should not be wide public access because the 
information contained in them could be damaging de maiziere said 
about 5000 stasi workers were used exclusively to listen to 
telephone conversations and the details in the files not only 
contain political views but information such as whether people were 
faithful to their spouses 
de maiziere will relinquish control of his country to west 
german chancellor helmut kohl on oct 3 
he said he has viewed his role as prime minister as that of a 
lawyer representing a very large client during the hard bargaining 
on the terms of unification and he would accept a similar role in 
a united germany 
however he said he has made no decision on whether to become 
one of the four east german ministers who will be added to kohls 
cabinet when the germanys unite 
meanwhile east germanys interior minister said today that he 
believed extremists from both the left and right were planning to 
disrupt unification celebrations next week in berlin 
petermichael diestel spoke hours after about 500 leftist 
protesters rampaged in central east berlin smashing windows at a 
major department store 
diestel speaking to reporters called monday nights incident a 
general rehearsal for disturbances he said were planned at the 
celebrations starting late next tuesday he did not say how he had 
learned of the plans 
</TEXT>
