unwilling to decide whether horton or cigarettes were more 
responsible for his death 
one of them jim upshaw told jurors in closing arguments monday 
that horton was a risktaker and he made a free choice to 
smoke 
the familys attorneys contended horton he was unaware of the 
magnitude of the risks 
the hortons wanted 2 million in actual damages and 15 million 
in punitive damages 
warning labels have been required on cigarette packages since 
1966 
