conservative prime minister brian mulroney heads 
into the new political season with an awesome array of worries 
ranging from rebellious indians and unpopular taxes to threats of a 
breakup of the confederation 
mulroney is in big trouble with voters scoring 14 percent or 
less in the polls but the opposition liberals have been unable to 
