<TEXT>
nasa said tuesday it will try to 
launch the shuttle discovery with a sunprobing satellite on oct 
6 while the search goes on for mysterious hydrogen leaks that have 
grounded columbia 
discovery is scheduled to lift off at 735 am with five 
astronauts who will send the european satellite on a fiveyear 
journey to study the suns polar regions it would be the first 
spacecraft to orbit the solar poles 
this date is a little successoriented and is dependent on not 
encountering any unusual problems said shuttle director robert 
crippen but i think the shuttle team has a good chance of making 
the 6th 
nasas last shuttle flight was in april when discovery carried 
the flawed hubble space telescope into orbit soon afterward the 
rest of the fleet columbia and atlantis were crippled by hydrogen 
leaks 
columbia is not expected to fly until late this year or early 
next year nasas fourth attempt in as many months to send columbia 
on an astronomy mission failed last week 
atlantis has been in the hangar since early august undergoing 
repairs for leaks in hydrogen lines between the orbiter and its 
external tank its classified pentagon mission originally 
scheduled for july is now set for early november 
nasa officials repeatedly have said they are confident 
discoverys fuel lines are leakfree because of the shuttles 
flight performance in april and the minimal amount of work 
performed since then in its engine compartment 
nasa faces an oct 23 launch deadline for discovery and the 
plutoniumpowered sun probe named for the legendary greek 
adventurer ulysses if discovery does not lift off by then the 
mission will have to wait until the planets are properly aligned 
again in late 1991 
to enter an orbit passing over the suns poles ulysses must 
travel to jupiter a 16month trip and use that planets gravity 
to throw it back toward the sun ulysses is expected to pass over 
the suns south pole in 1994 and the north pole the following year 
the white house on monday approved discoverys launch with 
ulysses such approval is necessary when radioisotope 
thermoelectric generators or rtgs are used 
ulysses one rtg will convert heat from 24 pounds of decaying 
plutonium into electricity antinuclear activists and 
environmentalists oppose the generators use saying a 
challengerlike accident would spread the deadly plutonium over 
florida 
