<TEXT>
the united states is considering a 
romanian offer to put up thousands of us troops on their way to 
and from the arabian peninsula in luxury resorts free of charge 
officials said tuesday 
the offer would apply through the winter and would be extended 
to british and canadian troops as well economics minister eugen 
dijmarescu said 
if the offer is accepted romania would become the first member 
of the crumbling sovietled warsaw pact to permit us and other 
nato troops on its territory 
the romanian proposal was revealed two days before the departure 
of president ion iliescu for the united states 
iliescu a former communist who took power during the december 
revolution that ousted nicolae ceausescu and won popular elections 
in may is seeking to repair his image in the united states 
an official at the us embassy described the romanian offer as 
a gesture of support for the west in the gulf crisis 
the official speaking on condition on anonymity said romanian 
officials contacted the embassy last week and offered randr 
facilities for american troops both in the mountains and on the 
black sea coast on favorable terms 
