it looks like the end of the road for the 
earthquakedamaged embarcadero freeway a doubledecker span 
likened to the berlin wall for the way it separates san franciscos 
downtown and waterfront 
the board of supervisors voted monday to tear down the milelong 
stretch of the road thats been closed since the 71magnitude 
quake did widespread damage in october 1989 the freeways concrete 
support columns were damaged 
the embarcadero freeway has been san franciscos environmental 
berlin wall supervisor bill maher said it has been a blight 
on our city and our waterfront ever since it was built 
at the time of the quake the embarcadero carried 60000 cars a 
day along the waterfront to chinatown the north beach restaurant 
district and fishermans wharf the citys prime tourist 
attraction 
chinatown merchants oppose its destruction because the highway 
made it easy for tourists and other customers to get there 
technically the boards 65 vote was strictly advisory but 
federal and state officials have made it clear they will go along 
with the citys decision 
no formal demolition request has been filed by the city mayor 
