<TEXT>
the marine corps has grounded four harrier jet 
fighterbombers similar to those sent to the persian gulf because 
of faulty sensors that stabilize the aircraft the service said 
tuesday 
the vertical takeoff av8b planes were found to have defective 
rate sensor assemblies a system which includes three 
gyroscopes and provides direction information for the jet said 
col stuart wagner 
its not critical to flying the aircraft safely but its 
something we want to fix wagner said of the assemblies similar 
to the power steering on a car 
the rate sensor assemblies are wearing out faster than expected 
he said 
wagner said the grounded harriers were based at kaneohe bay 
marine corps air station in hawaii but tuesday night the defense 
department said no harriers were based there 
the defense department spokesman army maj mike dibble said he 
was unable to determine immediately where the grounded planes were 
the action has no effect on the harriers deployed in saudi 
arabia as part of the us military buildup against iraq wagner 
said 
the announcement on the grounding came as the house government 
operations subcommittee on legislation and national security again 
examined procurement and testing irregularities by northrop corp 
involving the harrier jet and advanced cruise missile 
northrop pleaded guilty in february to 34 fraud charges and 
agreed to pay 17 million in fines which according to the justice 
department is the largest criminal fine ever imposed on a defense 
contractor 
the charges stemmed from northrops work on the harrier and the 
nucleararmed airlaunched cruise missile the navy which handles 
procurement for the marine corps suspended northrup from further 
contracts and recommended a suspension from all defense work the 
air force however is buying b2 stealth bombers made by northrup 
testimony before the house panel tuesday detailing the 
procurement and testing irregularities was similar to what the 
justice department told a house energy and commerce subcommittee in 
july 
witnesses tuesday described how northrop never performed life 
expectancy tests on the rate sensor assemblies 
the assemblies were supposed to have undergone a vibration test 
at 32 times the acceleration imparted by gravity but instead were 
tested at half that acceleration they also were to have been 
operated continuously for 4000 hours to determine life expectancy 
we decided that it would cost too much to perform this test at 
an outside lab howard hyde a former chief engineer with 
northrop who is serving a oneyear sentence for falsifying tests on 
the harrier jet said of the vibration tests 
no spare sensor assemblies are available forcing the marines to 
park the 22 million planes as problems arise no other company 
produces the assemblies 
the marine corps officer for the harrier program told the panel 
that it has waived the suspension against northrop to buy a package 
of spare rate sensor assemblies for 300000 
col james hart said the service is working out a contract with 
another manufacturer that will likely cost 1 million 
who will supply the new rate sensor assembly components to the 
the harriers back off the ground the corporation that bilked us to 
begin with complained rep john conyers dmich chairman of 
the government operations subcommittee 
it looks like business as usual for northrop it has a corner 
on the market and national security needs override all other 
considerations 
the marine corps has nearly 200 harriers made by 
mcdonnelldouglas corp under license from a british manufacturer 
the harriers needing no runway to take off can be based in 
forest clearings and other unorthodox places to provide close 
support and air cover for marine units 
their swiveling jet exhaust nozzles give them outsanding 
maneuverability in the air that enabled british pilots to dominate 
their argentine opponents in the 1982 falklands war 
