thanks to steve allen an entire generation soon 
will learn that the idea of hot young comedians doing live hip 
sketch comedy on a tv variety show is older than nbcs saturday 
night live 
at last another generation can wonder whether theres a fern in 
its creel on oct 1 ha the tv comedy network debuts the first 
of 100 halfhours from the steve allen show a live weekly 
variety show that ran headtohead against the ed sullivan show 
on sunday nights from 1956 to 1959 
elvis presley made his tv debut on the allen show but the 
program was known more for its daft inspired comedy by a troupe of 
brilliant comics that included don knotts louis nye tom poston 
pat harrington and allen himself 
we all had a kind of vibration of mutual craziness and 
creativity that first of all made our work pleasurable and 
secondly very effective allen said 
the show was a jumpingoff point for pop culture allens 
wordplay with the band smock smock smock and the casts 
doubletalk hows your fern on sunday night would echo in 
schools and businesses on monday 
for the record allen said he does not have a fern in his 
creel 
well i had it removed several years ago allen said but 
it didnt hurt much 
barumpbump 
when the sunday show started there were just three of us 
writing it stan burns herb sargent and myself allen said 
today a show like that would have literally 22 or 23 writers 
in four or five days we were putting together each week 
something that was literally on the level of a broadway musical 
comedy revue he said and yet we were so young and energetic 
and having such great fun we never even thought to complain about 
it 
believe it or not we were having such fun with it we never 
looked upon it as a burden it was hard work oh yeah but we loved 
it 
allen 67 is the author of 35 books three of them coming out 
this year and hes still one of americas most prolific popular 
music composers 
the ha shows came from his own collection 
i was saving them for my greatgrandchildren should they ever 
be curious as to what i did he said but a combination of 
economic and cultural factors has created a vacuum a market for 
the good comedy of that 1950 period 
the underlying sociological fact allen said is that todays 
generation is the first in human history to have been exposed to 
comedy since birth 
children are literally hearing group laughter and the verbal 
cues that occasion it as part of their early exposure to human 
language of any sort he said 
i think this must have something to do with the fact that when 
they get to be 5 and 6 and a little more discriminating they all 
expect comedy 
in an essay allen wrote back in the 50s for the atlantic 
monthly he remembers observing that there were only 50 comedians 
in show business 
just think the whole funny business was being taken 
care of by a little group that you could have fit on a school 
bus he said now we have over 2000 thats an explosive 
mushrooming growth 
many of todays comedy performers are funnier than the 
oldtimers no names of the oldtimers but that is not the 
problem what is highly objectionable now is the degree to 
which wit which was once characteristic of american comedy is 
being replaced by shock vulgarity 
vulgarity is creeping into tv comedy as well allen said 
viewers he said should try to induce a sense of guilt or shame in 
television executives who either are permitting or demanding 
shockvulgar tv shows 
even if it turned out that those who say hey dont knock it 
its the way to get ratings were right they still should be 
discouraged allen said 
somebody should still say to them does the condition of the 
national consciousness mean nothing to you is it all dollars and 
cents 
 
