asil nadir a turkishcypriot who built up his 
polly peck conglomerate over more than two decades is fighting a 
battle on two fronts as he tries to impede the erosion of the 
companys stock market value and his own business reputation 
the companys board of directors and the turkish government have 
rallied around the chairman and chief executive officer of polly 
peck a firm whose interests are as diverse as del monte pineapples 
and sansui stereos 
the companys shares dove 55 percent last thursday on rumors of 
a possible serious fraud office investigation into the company 
later that day nadir was interviewed by the office which 
investigates and prosecutes cases of serious fraud 
british newspaper reports in recent weeks have alleged the 
companys share price may have been supported illegally as was the 
case in the headlinemaking guinness scandal which resulted in a 
fiveyear prison term for the brewers former chairman 
the department of trade and industry is considering a request 
made sunday by polly pecks board for an independent inquiry into 
