research institute 
arco unveiled its new ecpremium on sept 6 calling theffuel 
the cleanest burning gasoline available in southern california 
environmentalists became concerned about the new formula after 
obtaining previously undisclosed results of arcos testing 
compared to conventional unleaded premium arco had said the new 
fuel reduced emissions of cancercausing benzene by 36 percent 
carbon monoxide by 28 percent and smogforming hydrocarbons by 21 
percent 
but the company made no mention of the 34 percent increase in 
emissions of 13butadiene and a possible 98 percent increase in 
smogforming nitrogen oxides 
arco confirmed the butadiene results monday the los angeles 
times reported in its tuesday editions however the company said 
the 98 percent nitrogen oxide increase was based on unreliable 
data 
butadiene used in manufacturing some rubber is a toxic 
component of tailpipe emissions that is considered less threatening 
to health than benzene 
