production as well as in publishing is getting a foothold in the 
broadcast television business with the tvx purchase 
in september 1989 paramount agreed to buy the 79 percent tvx 
stake that the investment firm salomon brothers held in a deal 
worth about 140 million 
it subsequently bought another 4 percent and offered in july to 
buy the remainder at 750 a share tvxs special committee 
rejected that offer 
