<TEXT>
boise cascade corp said tuesday it has 
tightened its procedures to head off unsolicited takeover bids 
the boisebased wood products company announced it has reduced 
the amount of stock a single person or group can obtain before 
triggering the compays shareholder rights plan 
under the revisions the plan will be triggered if a person or 
group obtains 15 percent of the companys voting securities down 
from 20 percent 
the revised plan encourages a potential acquirer to negotiate 
with the board of directors earlier than was likely under the 
previous plan the company said in a statement 
the new plan also lowers from 25 percent to 15 percent the 
amount of stock ownership that will trigger a process under which 
stockholders can exercise their right to acquire additional shares 
of stock at a market value equal to twice the exercise price of the 
right 
company officials said they adopted the revisions so they could 
better represent stockholder interests in the face of a takeover 
bid 
