the civil trial is scheduled to begin in november in us 
district court in philadelphia 
us magistrate edwin naythons ruled nippon was in contempt of 
court for violating an order requiring nippon to produce 
information related to the case allegheny ludlum said nippon has 
until oct 5 to pay the fine 
a contempt finding is rare particularly against a foreign 
corporation said allegheny ludlum attorney john williams 
the highgrade steel patent allegheny ludlum is seeking to 
protect in the lawsuit accounted for 200 million of the companys 
12 billion in 1989 sales said company spokesman bert delano 
</TEXT>
