<DOCNO> AP900925-0277 </DOCNO>
<TEXT>
conagra inc reported tuesday a 167 percent 
increase in earnings in the quarter that ended aug 26 boosted by 
a strong performance from its prepared foods segment 
contributing for the first time to conagras performance were 
the beatrice cos businesses huntwesson swifteckrich and 
beatrice cheese conagra acquired beatrice aug 14 
conagra reported net income for the first quarter of fiscal 1991 
of 5717 million or 45 cents per share on sales of 45 billion 
that compared with net income of 4897 million or 40 cents per 
share on sales of 4 billion for the same period last year 
the company realized a 21 million gain on nonrecurring items 
last fiscal year 
conagra officials said that virtually every one of its 
operations showed good earnings prepared foods the omahabased 
companys largest segment had a substantial operating profit 
beef pork chicken and turkey products also had profit growth 
while unit sales in the consumer frozen food business were up 
operating profit was down because of heavier spending on marketing 
company officials said 
operating profits in the agriproducts segment declined because 
heavy rains reduced plantings in some areas officials said 
</TEXT>
