<TEXT>
the board of directors of scheringplough 
corp tuesday authorized a buyout of up to 1 billion of the 
companys common stock 
market conditions have made stock in the pharmaceutical and 
health care company an exceptionally good value said robert p 
luciano the companys chairman and chief executive officer said 
in a news release 
the company expects to buy the shares on the open market 
according to the release 
last year scheringplough completed the sale of its european 
cosmetic businesses and divested a majority interest in its 
brazilian affiliate 
schering stock closed up 325 at 44 tuesday on the new york 
stock exchange its 52week low was 35 
</TEXT>
