<TEXT>
desoto inc is asking shareholders to approve 
a plan to sell off most of the manufacturers assets and terminate 
its pension plans in return for a onetime dividend of 3550 per 
share 
in documents filed with the securities and exchange commission 
and disclosed tuesday desoto outlined its list of issues for 
shareholders to vote on at the companys annual meeting oct 24 in 
chicago 
among them des plaines illbased desoto wants shareholder 
approval of a restructuring under which the company would sell 
substantialy all of its businesses including its domestic 
consumer paint business which has supplied sears roebuck and co 
for 80 years 
the companys detergent business would be the only operation 
retained by desoto which has been battling a hostile takeover by a 
new york investment group sutton holding corp 
desoto estimated that the partial liquidation and restructuring 
would raise about 222 million before taxes with 85 million 
earmarked to retire corporate debt 
the remainder would go toward paying a special cash dividend of 
3550 per share but desoto conceded that there was no 
assurance it would be able to pay the cash dividend 
it noted that its plan to terminate pension plans and recover 
some 28 million in excess assets is subject to approval by the 
internal revenue service and the pension benefit guaranty corp the 
federal agency that guarantees workers pensions much like the 
federal deposit insurance corp guarantees bank deposits 
</TEXT>
